%feature("docstring") OT::ExponentialFactory
"Exponential factory.

Available constructor:
    ExponentialFactory()

Let :math:`\bar{x}` be the sample mean. 
Let :math:`x_{(1)}` be the sample minimum. 
The parameter :math:`\gamma` is estimated by method of maximum 
likelihood, with asymptotic correction for bias:

.. math::
    :nowrap:

    \begin{eqnarray*}
      \hat{\gamma} = x_{(1)} - \frac{|x_{(1)}|}{2 + n}
    \end{eqnarray*}

The parameter :math:`\lambda` is estimated by method of moments:

.. math::
    :nowrap:

    \begin{eqnarray*}
      \hat{\lambda} = \frac{1}{\bar{x} - \hat{\gamma}}
    \end{eqnarray*}

When :math:`\gamma` is known, the estimator for :math:`\lambda` is equivalent 
to the method of maximum likelihood. 

See also
--------
DistributionFactory, Exponential"

